tabase/#type=cdb&wrestler=1426 |title=Champions Database-Matt Hughes |publisher=National Wrestling Hall of Fame |accessdate=2012-07-12}}</ref>\n**[[NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] 158&nbsp;lb - 5th place <small>out of [[Eastern Illinois University]]</small> (1997)<ref name=\"Wrestler Matt Hughes\"/>\n*'''[[National Junior College Athletic Association]]'''\n**[[NJCAA#Halls of fame|NJCAA Hall of Fame]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://matt-hughes.com/blog1/2012/03/01/njcaa-hall-of-fame |title=NJCAA Hall of Famer |date=2012-03-01 |publisher=Matt-Hughes.com |accessdate=2012-09-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121017080604/http://matt-hughes.com/blog1/2012/03/01/njcaa-hall-of-fame/ |archivedate=2012-10-17 }}</ref>\n**[[NJCAA]] All-American Team (Two times)<ref name=\"NJCAA career\">{{cite web |url=http://69.56.199.5/pr/feed/02212012.html |title=Former Lincoln College Wrestler Matt Hughes to Be Inducted in the NJCAA Wrestling Hall of Fame |date=2012-02-21 |accessdate=2012-09-26 |publisher=Lincoln College }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n**[[NJCAA]] Division I 158&nbsp;lb - 5th place <small>out of [[Southwestern Illinois College]]</small> (1994)<ref name=\"NJCAA career\"/>\n**[[NJCAA]] Division I 158&nbsp;lb - 3rd place <small>out of [[Lincoln College (Illinois)|Lincoln College]]</small> (1995)<ref name=\"NJCAA career\"/>\n*'''[[Eastern Illinois University]]'''\n**EIU Athletic Hall of Fame<ref>{{cite web |url=http://matt-hughes.com/blog1/2008/09/15/eiu-hall-of-fame |title=EIU Hall of Famer |publisher=Matt-Hughes.com |date=2008-09-15 |accessdate=2012-09-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521170731/http://matt-hughes.com/blog1/2008/09/15/eiu-hall-of-fame/ |archivedate=2011-05-21 }}</ref>\n*'''[[Illinois High School Association]]'''\n**[[Illinois High School Association|IHSA]] Class A State Wrestling Champion 145&nbsp;lb (1991)<ref name=\"IHSA\">{{cite web |url=http: